President Donald J. Trump has declared a state of emergency in Mississippi due to the emergency conditions resulting from Hurricane Sally. This declaration authorizes the Department of Homeland Security, specifically the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA), to coordinate disaster relief efforts in order to alleviate the hardship and suffering caused by the emergency. FEMA is authorized to provide equipment and resources necessary to alleviate the impacts of the emergency, and emergency protective measures will be provided at 75 percent federal funding. Brett H. Howard has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. For further information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.